The paper discusses the use of automated planning techniques for goal recognition, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of heuristics and filtering methods, which are common in machine learning (cs.LG) and robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses the evaluation of the proposed approaches in classical planning domains, which falls under software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL).
